OL,3,CJacob Rees-Mogg among Tory MPs whose
OL,4,CGB News programme broke Ofcom's rules
OL,6,FA further episode of Sir Jacob's State
OL,7,FOf The Nation was not investigated
OL,8,Fbecause it did not raise issues under
OL,9,Fthe rules, according to Ofcom.
OL,11,FThe media watchdog said that because
OL,12,Fthe politicians "acted as newsreaders,
OL,13,Fnews interviewers or news reporters in
OL,14,Fsequences which clearly constituted
OL,15,Fnews ` including reporting breaking
OL,16,Fnews events ` without exceptional
OL,17,Fjustification, news was, therefore,
OL,18,Fnot presented with due impartiality".
