OL,3,CJacob Rees-Mogg among Tory MPs whose
OL,4,CGB News programme broke Ofcom's rules
OL,6,FIt went on: "Politicians have an
OL,7,Finherently partial role in society and
OL,8,Fnews content presented by them is
OL,9,Flikely to be viewed by audiences in
OL,10,Flight of that perceived bias.
OL,12,F"In our view, the use of politicians
OL,13,Fto present the news risks undermining
OL,14,Fthe integrity and credibility of
OL,15,Fregulated broadcast news."
OL,17,FIn response, GB News said it was
OL,18,F"deeply concerned by the decision"
OL,19,Fbefore vowing to "raise this directly
OL,20,Fwith the regulator in the strongest
OL,21,Fpossible terms."
